description: Authentic Brick + Beam loft at '319 A St' in Boston’s coveted Fort Point neighborhood, ideally situated at the crossroads of the Seaport + Waterfront districts, offering cinematic North-by-Northwest views from its enviable corner layout. With its soaring 13ft ceilings + 16 expansive windows showcasing century old timbers, its rugged bricks are bathed in natural light. This smart home is decked out with cutting-edge Wi-Fi enabled technology including Lutron Roller Blackout Shades, mood-enhancing Phillips Hue strip-lighting & Ecobee Thermostat, easily integrated with an Apple HomeKit. The sleek modern kitchen designed for culinary enthusiasts offers SS appliances, honed black granite counters + Zebrawood cabinetry. Primary-BR suite features a customized California walk-in and ceiling mounted projector. Guest-BR easily double as a home office as needed. With an elevator, roof deck, bike room & welcoming lounge, this boutique complex flawlessly embodies the vibrant essence of city living.
